                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d58">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.<gloss target="#t_BC1">BC</gloss>/8–1448:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in France</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-08-18T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 18, 1948—4 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3182. We are following suggestion last para <gloss target="#t_urtel1"
                        >urtel</gloss> 4214 Aug 14,<note n="1" xml:id="d58fn1">Officials at the
                        French Foreign Ministry had expressed a desire to inform the Benelux
                        countries of the United States position regarding the Security Council seat
                        being vacated by Belgium, namely that it was impractical to support the
                        candidacy of Luxembourg for this seat (501.<gloss target="#t_BC1"
                        >BC</gloss>/8–1448).</note> and approaching Benelux countries. Please inform
                    French, while we have no objection their further discussion matter Benelux, we
                    would prefer our position not be mentioned by them pending opportunity for us to
                    consult on matter wider basis. For your info Brit have not given us definite
                    indication their thinking, although have implied Norway might become their first
                    choice.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
